RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 11500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MILEYS BLUECAT prompted the pace from the two path then fell back on the turn but made a rebid from the inside in the stretch to draw clear in the late stretch. ABRAAJ MIRAGE vied for the lead from the inside then checked slightly at the three furlong pole and dropped back but was able to pass tiring ones in the stretch. WARRIORS HERO broke out slightly at the start but showed no early speed through the turn, went four or five wide in upper stretch for a late run and was just up for the show. BARBARIAN went to the front to set a pressured pace from the three path then was headed at the quarter pole and fought off DECIMATE on the outside but was not able to fend off the inside rival and tired. DECIMATE was off the pace in the early stages then made a three to four wide bid on the turn to engage the leader but was empty in the drive. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS POSTED INTO THE RUNNING OF THE RACE NEAR THE THREE FURLONG POLE, THE JOCKEY OF ABRAAJ MIRAGE CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE JOCKEY OF MILEYS BLUECAT FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE NEAR THE THREE EIGHTHS POLE, AFTER A STEWARDS REVIEW THE CLAIM OF FOULS WAS DISALLOWED AND NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.
